summary: An ordinance fixing the rate of taxes to be levied and levying the taxes upon all taxable property, both real and personal, in the City of Seattle, in order to raise sufficient revenue to carry on the different departments and activities of the municipal government, and to provide for the general lien bonds interest and redemption requirements of the ensuing fiscal year, beginning the first day of January 1934, and ending on the 31st day of December 1934.
